Changing the encoding

The first parameter of the main method is the name of a file encoded in Windows-1251.
The second parameter of the main method is the name of a file to which you need to write the contents of the first file,
but encoded in UTF-8.

Requirements:
•	The program must not read data from the keyboard.
•	The program should not display data on the screen.
•	The program must write data to a file.
•	The contents of the second file must match the contents of the first file except for the encoding (UTF-8).